transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hello, Mr. Gibson?

Speaker 2: Yep, this is me.

Speaker 1: Yes, I just pulled your prescription.

Speaker 2: I see that you have a prescription from Dr. Sanderson for Viagra 100mg, 10 tablets, every 30 days.

Speaker 1: How can I help you, Mr. Gibson?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I want to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Any health concern, or you just don't need it every 30 days?

Speaker 2: No, I just don't want it anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Alright, you have the possibility, because I have to tell you that, to pause the prescription so you can order as needed.

Speaker 1: So, we advise the pharmacy to stop the initial 30 days, 10 tablets, so you can just order as needed, maybe once or twice a year.

Speaker 2: No, no, no. I want you to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Alright, so I'm canceling the doctor's prescription.

Speaker 2: We advise of the price change.

Speaker 1: If the company takes your order, they're going to apply the cost of a new doctor consultation probably in the price, because we're losing that one right now.

Speaker 2: So, everything has been cancelled, and you're all set.

Speaker 1: Alright, thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
